I have ears but cannot hear. What am I?:
corn
I'm tall when I'm young, and I'm short when I'm old. What am I?:
candle
What comes once in a minute, twice in a moment, but never in a thousand years?:
m
What gets wetter the more it dries?:
towel
What can travel around the world while staying in the corner?:
stamp
What has many layers but isn't a cake,and is often found in the ground?:
onion
What can you catch but not throw?:
cold
What has one head, one foot, and four legs?:
bed
I have keys but open no locks. I have space but no room. You can enter but you can't go inside. What am I?:
keyboard
What is so fragile that saying its name breaks it?:
silence
What comes down but never goes up?:
rain
I speak without a mouth and hear without ears. I have no body, but I come alive with the wind. What am I?:
echo
What is full of holes but still holds a lot of weight?:
sponge
What begins with T, ends with T, and has T in it?:
teapot
I can be cracked, made, told and played. What am I?
joke
What has a head, a tail, but no body?:
coin
What runs but never walks, has a bed but never sleeps?:
river
What comes up but never goes down?:
age
What can be cracked, made, told, and played, but never seen?:
secret
What has a neck but no head?:
bottle
What is always in front of you but can't be seen?:
future
What can be broken but never held?:
promise
What word is spelled incorrectly in every dictionary?:
incorrectly
What has cities, but no houses; forests, but no trees; and rivers; but no water?:
map
What begins with an E, ends with an E, but only contains one letter?:
envelope